Interface StackADT<E>

Type Parameters:
E - The object that is held in the stack.
public interface StackADT<E>
last in first out. used as a basis for the stack structure that we will implement for part 2
Version:
1.1
Author:
Dat, Airzy, Eric

  • Method Details

    • pop

      E pop()
      Method to pop(remove) the top(last) value of the stack. Precondition: Have at least one value in the stack. Postcondition: The last value of the stack is removed from the stack.
      Returns:
      the value that was removed from the stack.
      Throws:
      NoSuchElementException - if there are no values within the stack.

    • push

      void push(E obj)
      Method to push(add) a value to the top of the stack. Precondition: An existing stack must be present to be pushed to. Postcondition: The stack gains an additional value at the end of the stack.
      Parameters:
      obj - : the obj is added to the end of the stack

    • peek

      E peek()
      Method to get the value at the top of the stack without altering the stack. Precondition: An existing stack must be present to be peeked at. Postcondition: The value at the top of the stack is determined.
      Returns:
      the value at the top of the stack.
      Throws:
      NoSuchElementException - if there are no values within the stack.

    • size

      int size()
      Method to determine the size (how many values) of the stack. Precondition: None Postcondition: The size and the number of values inside the stack is determined.
      Returns:
      size of the stack

    • isEqualTo

      boolean isEqualTo(StackADT<E> otherStack)
      Method to compare two stacks and determine if they have the same exact values in the same order. Precondition: Two stacks are available to be compared. Postcondition: The result if the stacks are the same or not.
      Parameters:
      otherStack - : The other stack to be compared to.
      Returns:
      True if the stacks are the same. False if the stacks are different.

    • toArray

      Object[] toArray()
      Method to convert the stack into an array. Precondition: An existing stack must be present. Postcondition: An array of all the contents from the stack is created.
      Returns:
      the array that has the same components as the stack it was based on.

    • search

      int search(E obj)
      Method to search where the value is in the stack. Precondition: A stack must already be present. Postcondition: The position of the value is stated.
      Parameters:
      obj - : the specific value to be searched for within the stack.
      Returns:
      the int position of where it is located within the stack. It also returns -1 if the value is not found.

    • contains

      boolean contains(E obj)
      Method to determine if a specific value exists within the stack. Precondition: A stack must already be present. Postcondition: Determine if a value exists or not.
      Parameters:
      obj - : the specific value to searched for to determine whether or not it exists within the stack.
      Returns:
      True if the value exists within the stack. False if it does not.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Method to check if the stack is empty or not. Precondition: None Postcondition: Determine if the stack is empty or not.
      Returns:
      True if the stack is empty. False if not.

    • clear

      void clear()
      Method to clear the entire stack of all its contents. Precondition: None Postcondition: The stack is now empty without any values within the stack.
